subSubSection.paragraph:
Prostomium short, palps biarticulated, separate, palpostyles massive knobs with ventrolateral papilla (
Fig. 11A
). Three subequal antennae, laterals arise from base of palps, median one posteriorly placed. Four tiny eyespots on right side of the prostomium (see comments below).

Parapodia with subequal fusiform cirri, setal lobe in median setigers as long as half the length of dorsal cirri, posteriorly becomes slightly longer, towards the pygidium become smaller. Notospines start at setiger 21 (23 on the left side). Pygidium with terminal anus (
Fig. 11G
); two lateroventral anal cirri as long as the previous three segments. Neurosetae mainly limbate setae but most broken, furcate setae were not seen. Everted pharynx short, globose, smooth, it is two setigers long. Non-everted pharynx about 11 setigers long.
